The equation $|z - 12| + |z - 5i| = 13$ represents all points $z$ whose distances to $12$ and $5i$ add up to $13$. Geometrically, this is an ellipse with foci at $12$ and $5i,$ and major axis of length $13$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, F1, F2, Z;

A = (12,0);
B = (0,5);
F1 = A;
F2 = B;
Z = (5.5,3);

draw(Circle(F1,13 - abs(F1 - F2)/2));
draw(Circle(F2,abs(F1 - F2)/2));
draw((-2,0)--(16,0));
draw((0,-2)--(0,10));
draw(F1--F2);
draw(F1--Z--F2);

label("$12$", F1, S);
label("$5i$", F2, W);
label("$z$", Z, NE);
[/asy]

The minimum value of $|z|$ occurs when $z$ is the point on the ellipse closest to the origin.  This point lies on the line segment connecting the foci $12$ and $5i.$

