Let $z = a + bi.$  Then
\[|z - 12| + |z - 5i| = 13.\]This simplifies to
\[\sqrt{(a - 12)^2 + b^2} + \sqrt{a^2 + (b - 5)^2} = 13.\]Since $z$ lies on the line segment connecting $12$ and $5i,$ $a$ and $b$ are proportional.  Let $a = 12t$ and $b = 5t,$ for some $t.$  Then
\[\sqrt{(12t - 12)^2 + 25t^2} + \sqrt{144t^2 + (5t - 5)^2} = 13.\]This simplifies to
\[\sqrt{229t^2 - 288t + 144} + \sqrt{169t^2 - 50t + 25} = 13.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[229t^2 - 288t + 144 + 169t^2 - 50t + 25 + 2 \sqrt{(229t^2 - 288t + 144)(169t^2 - 50t + 25)} = 169.\]Then
\[2 \sqrt{(229t^2 - 288t + 144)(169t^2 - 50t + 25)} = -384t^2 + 338t - 1.\]Squaring both sides again, we get
\[4(229t^2 - 288t + 144)(169t^2 - 50t + 25) = 147456t^4 - 272640t^3 + 163844t^2 - 2716t + 1.\]This simplifies to $147456t^4 - 272640t^3 + 163844t^2 - 2716t + 1 = 0.$  We can factor this as
\[(16t - 1)^2 (9216t^2 - 2720t + 1) = 0.\]The quadratic factor has no real roots, so $t = \frac{1}{16}.$  Then $z = \frac{3}{4} + \frac{5}{16} i,$ so
\[|z| = \sqrt{\frac{9}{16} + \frac{25}{256}} = \boxed{\frac{13}{16}}.\]

